The new L...

29
00:01:51,654 --> 00:01:52,655
It can't be. ...!

30
00:01:53,448 --> 00:01:55,241
Are you serious, Near?

31
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:57,702
Yes. But even though I say
that I'm serious,

32
00:01:57,785 --> 00:01:59,537
I'm only seven percent sure...

33
00:02:01,706 --> 00:02:05,960
Commander Rester, we have to make
assumptions during investigations.

34
00:02:06,502 --> 00:02:08,713
If we're wrong,
we can just say we're sorry.

35
00:02:09,172 --> 00:02:12,175
JUSTICE

36
00:02:15,553 --> 00:02:19,766
There have been fewer crimes
in Japan lately.

37
00:02:20,516 --> 00:02:22,143
My dad told me that if
you do something bad,

38
00:02:22,226 --> 00:02:24,312
your name will be posted
on the internet

39
00:02:24,395 --> 00:02:28,399
- and Kira will kill you.
- What's your name? Come on.

40
00:02:28,483 --> 00:02:30,693
If you don't tell us your name,
we can't file a report.

41
00:02:31,069 --> 00:02:33,655
Give me a break!
Anything but my name!

42
00:02:34,697 --> 00:02:36,991
I'm going to post your names
on the internet.

43
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:46,292
KIRA, PLEASE KILL...

44
00:03:04,519 --> 00:03:09,607
<i>I will declare this right here!
Kira is justice!</i>

45
00:03:11,859 --> 00:03:14,320
KIRA'S KINGDOM

46
00:03:16,072 --> 00:03:19,867
<i>It is absolutely true that
I was appointed</i>

47
00:03:20,243 --> 00:03:21,786
<i>by Kira as his spokesperson.</i>

48
00:03:22,995 --> 00:03:25,957
<i>Some people may try to kill me
because of this.</i>

49
00:03:26,958 --> 00:03:28,042
<i>But!</i>

50
00:03:28,501 --> 00:03:29,794
<i>I am prepared to risk my life</i>

51
00:03:29,794 --> 00:03:34,090
NEW JAPANESE TASK FORCE
HEADQUARTERS

52
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:34,882
It's the end of the world...

53
00:03:36,092 --> 00:03:40,263
<i>Persecufing ifira is an unforgivable e02'
and should be considered a crime.</i>

54
00:03:40,471 --> 00:03:42,807
We should really kill this guy.

55
00:03:43,516 --> 00:03:46,018
<i>If you see someone trying to find Kira,
whether that person is a police officer,</i>

56
00:03:46,102 --> 00:03:47,478
<i>- Oh, the preskienfs press conference. ..
- a regular citizen, or a criminal,</i>

57
00:03:47,562 --> 00:03:49,105
<i>- is about to begin.
- bring charges against them!</i>

58
00:03:50,982 --> 00:03:52,483
What could it be about?

59
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:55,528
They said that it was
an announcement to the world.

60
00:03:56,446 --> 00:03:58,906
You're always watching TV,
aren't you?

61
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:03,536
<i>We, the United States of America...</i>

62
00:04:07,206 --> 00:04:08,458
<i>Could it be?!</i>

63
00:04:09,792 --> 00:04:13,504
<i>Acknowledge Kira and will
do nothing to stand in his way...</i>

64
00:04:17,091 --> 00:04:19,218
Damn! This is insane!

65
00:04:19,677 --> 00:04:23,514
<i>I did it! The United States
has bowed down to Kira...</i>

66
00:04:24,015 --> 00:04:26,100
What is he talking about?

67
00:04:26,434 --> 00:04:27,852
Is he afraid of Kira?!

68
00:04:28,102 --> 00:04:30,563
- Mr. President, explain this!
- When was this decided?!

69
00:04:30,646 --> 00:04:31,856
- Give us more details!
- Explain yourself!

70
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:33,983
- Are you saying that Kira is justice?!
- That's right!

71
00:04:34,066 --> 00:04:36,527
Justice? I didn't say that.

72
00:04:37,028 --> 00:04:39,947
But war no longer exists
because of Kira...

73
00:04:40,031 --> 00:04:41,824
Criminal organizations are in
a state of ruin,

74
00:04:41,908 --> 00:04:44,869
not only in the United States,
but around the world...

75
00:04:45,328 --> 00:04:49,832
<i>There is no mistake. Whoever defies
Kira directly will be killed.</i>

76
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:52,543
<i>We know that Kira does not
stand for justice, but...</i>

77
00:04:52,794 --> 00:04:56,506
<i>as a country, we will not take
any actions to catch Kira.</i>

78
00:04:56,589 --> 00:04:58,132
<i>T-That's the same thing!
You idiot!</i>

79
00:04:58,216 --> 00:04:59,467
<i>You just announced that
you acknowledged Kira!</i>

80
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:00,676
<i>Please explain!</i>

81
00:05:00,802 --> 00:05:01,803
<i>Are you running away?!</i>

82
00:05:01,886 --> 00:05:03,554
<i>How can you call yourself
the leader of our country?!</i>

83
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:05,515
I don't believe it.

84
00:05:05,598 --> 00:05:09,310
This is the U.S. we're talking about...
That was the president's statement!

85
00:05:10,061 --> 00:05:12,688
Umm... I'd like to ask
a serious question.

86
00:05:13,022 --> 00:05:14,607
What is it all of a sudden, Matsuda?

87
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:16,734
So you're saying that
you're not always serious?

88
00:05:17,443 --> 00:05:20,571
In the depths of your heart,
do you think that Kira is evil?

89
00:05:20,863 --> 00:05:22,907
- What?!
- What do you mean, Matsuda?!

90
00:05:23,908 --> 00:05:27,578
Honestly... I don't think
he's completely evil.

91
00:05:28,246 --> 00:05:30,414
Do you believe that Kira is justice?

92
00:05:31,415 --> 00:05:32,542
I don't know...

93
00:05:33,376 --> 00:05:36,796
But I think that Kira is fighting evil.

94
00:05:37,505 --> 00:05:39,924
The world has definitely
become a good place

95
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:42,093
for people who live honestly.

96
00:05:42,176 --> 00:05:43,511
You're wrong, Matsuda.

97
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:47,765
They're afraid of the carnage.
It's not true peace...

98
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:50,768
I know. I know that!

99
00:05:51,102 --> 00:05:56,023
But I understand the feelings
of those who call Kira a savior!

100
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:57,608
I've always been...

101
00:05:57,692 --> 00:06:00,111
A weak person...

102
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:04,574
But I'm a detective.
I can't accept Kira...

103
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:09,078
I understand that and want
to catch him as a part of my job.

104
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:13,958
I'm probably messed up for not being
able to completely denounce him.

105
00:06:15,751 --> 00:06:17,503
There's nothing wrong
with you, Mr. Matsuda.

106
00:06:19,005 --> 00:06:21,257
Light, you too?
What are you talking about?

107
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:25,845
Kira probably knows that
what he's doing is evil...

108
00:06:27,305 --> 00:06:31,017
He'll change the world even
if he becomes a martyr...

109
00:06:31,851 --> 00:06:33,769
That is the form of justice
that Kira has chosen...

110
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:36,105
That's probably what Kira thinks.

111
00:06:37,732 --> 00:06:41,444
It's not our business to debate
whether Kira is good or evil.

112
00:06:42,445 --> 00:06:44,363
We just have to catch Kira.

113
00:06:45,865 --> 00:06:50,536
If Kira is caught, he is evil.
If Kira rules the world, he is justice.

114
00:06:55,207 --> 00:06:59,879
<i>But the world is rapidly
going over to Kira's side.</i>

115
00:07:01,380 --> 00:07:03,174
<i>Soon Kira will be justice.</i>

116
00:07:06,135 --> 00:07:07,803
What will happen to us?

117
00:07:08,387 --> 00:07:11,307
We'll be dissolved because
of that chicken of a president...

118
00:07:12,350 --> 00:07:16,145
No, he's not even a chicken.
He's less than a maggot.

119
00:07:19,565 --> 00:07:20,650
<i>You've got to be kidding.</i>

120
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:23,235
<i>There's no way that
accepting Kira can be good.</i>

121
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,309
You're alive?

122
00:07:58,813 --> 00:07:59,897
Near!

123
00:08:04,485 --> 00:08:05,569
What should we do?

124
00:08:05,653 --> 00:08:06,737
Let him in.

125
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:19,375
Welcome Mello...

126
00:08:19,709 --> 00:08:20,835
Put down your gun!

127
00:08:25,756 --> 00:08:27,925
Everyone, please put
down your guns.

128
00:08:28,676 --> 00:08:30,803
It is meaningless for
us to shed blood here.

129
00:08:31,887 --> 00:08:34,849
But Mello killed the others.

130
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:36,767
Don't make me repeat myself.

131
00:08:37,810 --> 00:08:40,396
Our goal is to catch Kira...

132
00:08:40,896 --> 00:08:43,983
Right now, killing Mello
will not benefit us.

133
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:47,653
All right...

134
00:08:50,614 --> 00:08:53,367
Have things gone as
you've planned, Near?

135
00:08:53,868 --> 00:08:56,078
Yes. You've heard from
Lidner, haven't you?

136
00:08:56,328 --> 00:08:57,663
About the Second L...

137
00:08:58,622 --> 00:09:01,125
I've pretty much figured out
who Kira is

138
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:02,710
because of everything you've done.

139
00:09:05,046 --> 00:09:06,047
Near!

140
00:09:08,007 --> 00:09:11,177
I'm not a tool for you to use
to solve the puzzle.

141
00:09:12,595 --> 00:09:15,639
Mello, shoot me if you want.

142
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:24,815
Mello! If you shoot Near,
we'll have no choice but to shoot you.

143
00:09:25,357 --> 00:09:29,111
What'll happen if you both die?
Only Kira will be happy.

144
00:09:32,448 --> 00:09:34,033
That's true.

145
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:38,329
Near, I just came to get
the photograph you have of me.

146
00:09:38,913 --> 00:09:43,375
Yes, this is the photograph.
There's only one, no copies.

147
00:09:43,834 --> 00:09:46,921
I've already dealt with everyone

148
00:09:47,004 --> 00:09:49,006
who knows your face at
Wammy's house and elsewhere.

149
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:52,176
I can't say I'm a hundred percent
certain, but...

150
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:54,929
it's safe to say you won't
be killed by the notebook.

151
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:59,725
Is that all, Mello?

152
00:10:03,854 --> 00:10:04,939
Near...

153
00:10:15,032 --> 00:10:18,744
I...have no intention
of working with you.

154
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:20,746
I know.

155
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:25,793
But it'll upset me to receive this picture
without giving anything in return.

156
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:30,965
The killer notebook...
It's a Shinigami's notebook.

157
00:10:31,215 --> 00:10:34,051
Whoever touches it,
is able to see the Shihigami.

158
00:10:35,886 --> 00:10:38,264
- That's crazy!
- Who would believe that?!

159
00:10:38,347 --> 00:10:39,723
I believe him.

160
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:43,519
What good would it be for
Mello to tell a lie like that?

161
00:10:44,061 --> 00:10:48,274
He would, at least tell a better lie,
or something that has some truth to it.

162
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:50,067
Therefore, Shinigami really exist.

163
00:10:51,026 --> 00:10:52,987
The notebook I had
was one that belonged

164
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:55,781
to someone other than a Shinigami...

165
00:10:56,323 --> 00:10:59,451
Also. . .there were fake rules within
the rules written in it.

166
00:11:00,578 --> 00:11:02,913
That's all I can tell you.

167
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:16,552
Near.

168
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,720
Mello...

169
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,311
Which of us is going to get Kira first?

170
00:11:26,145 --> 00:11:27,479
The race is on...

171
00:11:28,189 --> 00:11:30,357
Our destination is the same.

172
00:11:30,983 --> 00:11:32,526
I'll be waiting for you...

173
00:11:33,194 --> 00:11:34,236
Yes.

174
00:11:57,092 --> 00:11:58,302
<i>A fake rule...</i>

175
00:11:58,969 --> 00:12:02,348
<i>Judging from previous events,
there's no doubt that...</i>

176
00:12:02,431 --> 00:12:04,892
<i>the notebook can cause heart attacks
and control its victims, to a degree.</i>

177
00:12:04,975 --> 00:12:07,144
<i>As for burning or
tearing up the notebook...</i>

178
00:12:07,228 --> 00:12:10,564
<i>The notebook still exists and
there is no way to test it.</i>

179
00:12:10,898 --> 00:12:12,024
In that case...

180
00:12:19,073 --> 00:12:20,658
<i>The fake rule is the rule</i>

181
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:24,578
<i>that a person will die if he doesn't
write a name within thirteen days...</i>

182
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:29,541
Gevanni.

183
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:31,585
Get me L.

184
00:12:31,961 --> 00:12:33,045
Yes.

185
00:12:35,464 --> 00:12:36,507
It's from Near.

186
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:38,801
Yes?

187
00:12:38,884 --> 00:12:40,928
<i>L, we've caught Mello.</i>

188
00:12:42,179 --> 00:12:43,514
But he escaped.

189
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:46,892
<i>However, we were able to
interrogate him a little.</i>

190
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:50,187
He didn't escape.
You let him escape.

191
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:51,522
<i>Isn't that right?</i>

192
00:12:51,605 --> 00:12:53,691
No, he really did escape.

193
00:12:54,483 --> 00:12:57,987
By the way, Mello said that there is
a Shinigami attached to the notebook.

194
00:12:59,238 --> 00:13:02,116
<i>Have you been able to
confirm any such entity?</i>

195
00:13:03,284 --> 00:13:06,203
Yes. Shinigami do exist.

196
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:10,708
I kept it a secret because
I didn't think that you'd believe me.

197
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:14,336
<i>I'd like to talk to the Shinigami
about some things.</i>

198
00:13:14,795 --> 00:13:16,672
I don't want to talk.

199
00:13:17,214 --> 00:13:19,717
The thing that bothers me
the most is the fact that

200
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,887
there is a fake rule among
the rules written within the notebook.

201
00:13:25,055 --> 00:13:26,056
There's a fake?

202
00:13:26,348 --> 00:13:30,519
<i>Yes. L, tell me your thoughts...</i>

203
00:13:30,978 --> 00:13:33,605
<i>If there is a fake rule,
which one do you think it is?</i>

204
00:13:36,317 --> 00:13:39,820
By elimination,
it would have to be the one

205
00:13:39,903 --> 00:13:44,450
that requires the owner of the notebook
to write a name within 13 days, or die.

206
00:13:44,992 --> 00:13:48,287
<i>I thought you'd say that.
I think so too.</i>

207
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:55,711
Shinigami. ls there a fake rule among
the rules written within the notebook?

208
00:13:56,295 --> 00:13:57,755
No, there aren't any.

209
00:13:59,465 --> 00:14:01,800
So there's a Shinigami there?

210
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:03,969
Yes.

211
00:14:04,053 --> 00:14:05,262
<i>Isee“.</i>

212
00:14:06,221 --> 00:14:08,057
I pretty much get the picture.

213
00:14:09,016 --> 00:14:13,395
In other words, Kira is there and
he's making the Shihigami lie.

214
00:14:14,021 --> 00:14:16,565
<i>This guy's amazing.
He got it right...</i>

215
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:22,988
Even if the Shinigami is lying,
it doesn't mean anything.

216
00:14:23,614 --> 00:14:26,867
No. It would mean that it was
meaningless to detain Light.

217
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:30,913
If the rule that a person has to
continue writing names is fake,

218
00:14:31,038 --> 00:14:34,833
it makes it meaningless that he spent
more than 13 days doing nothing.

219
00:14:37,294 --> 00:14:39,296
But that's wrong!

220
00:14:39,463 --> 00:14:41,882
There's no way that Light is Kira.

221
00:14:42,216 --> 00:14:43,759
The Deputy Director confirmed that

222
00:14:43,842 --> 00:14:46,720
he didn't have a notebook
and passed away...

223
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:58,399
<i>Well then, how about
testing it in this way?</i>

224
00:14:58,982 --> 00:15:01,819
I will write Mello's name
in the notebook.

225
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:08,659
<i>When Mello dies,
and if I die 13 days later, Kira wins.</i>

226
00:15:08,992 --> 00:15:10,828
<i>I don't mind.</i>

227
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:12,621
What's this?

228
00:15:12,704 --> 00:15:13,956
So it's just a matter of
winning or losing?

229
00:15:14,331 --> 00:15:18,836
Even if testing the 13-day rule
benefits the Kira investigation,

230
00:15:19,044 --> 00:15:21,255
there shouldn't be any drawbacks.

231
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:24,383
I shall put my life on the line.

232
00:15:25,092 --> 00:15:29,346
<i>If I reject this offer on my own,
it will give a bad impression...</i>

233
